title: Latvia: Dziesma 2013 results revealed
text:
Latvia: Dziesma 2013 results revealed
Latvia: Dziesma 2013 results revealed
Source: esctoday.com, LTV
LTV the Latvian national broadcaster has revealed the results of all 3 Dziesma shows; the semifinals and final. Last Saturday PeR won the 2013 Latvian national final and will now represent Latvia at the forthcoming Eurovision Song Contest in Malmö.
Latvian national selection for Eurovision Song Contest has finished on February 16 in Ventspils – PeR with song Here We Go will enter the stage on May 16 in Malmö.
Latvian Television reveals the results of all heats of Dziesma 2013 – both semi finals, the final and the superfinal.
Results of the first semi final
First semi final of Dziesma 2013 took place on February 8. Jury was entitled to give points to the songs (1st place – 1 point, 2nd place – 2 points etc) determining its position. The same principle was applied to the results of the televote. The total was made by adding up the points given by jury and televote (50% : 50%). In case of a draw the favourite of the televote was preferred.
Jury of the first semi final: Aija Strazdiņa, Aija Vītoliņa Ieva Rozentāle, Lara Bellerose (Belgium), Ģirts Lūsis, Valters Pūce, Jegors Jerohomovičs, Kārlis Auzāns, Jānis Palkavnieks.

Results of the second semi final
On February 9 the second semi final of Dziesma 2013 was broadcast on LTV 1. Jury was entitled to give points to the songs (1st place – 1 point, 2nd place – 2 points etc) determining its position. The same principle was applied to the results of the televote. The total was made by adding up the points given by jury and televote (50% : 50%). In case of a draw the favourite of the televote was preferred. Songs were judged by a jury consisting of: Aija Strazdiņa, Aija Vītoliņa, Lara Bellerose (Belgium), Vineta Elksne, Ģirts Lūsis, Valters Frīdenbergs, Anmary, Valters Pūce, Jegors Jerohomovičs.

Results of the Final and Superfinal
The final of Dziesma 2013 had a live broadcast on LTV on February 16. It had two heats – final and superfinal. Jury was entitled to give points to the songs (1st place – 1 point, 2nd place – 2 points etc) determining its position. The same principle was applied to the results of the televote. The total was made by adding up the points given by jury and televote (50% : 50%). In case of a draw the favourite of the televote was preferred.
The jury of the final and superfinal: producer of music videos – Aija Strazdiņa, singer and vocal teacher – Vineta Elksne,producer of music and culture programs at LTV – Ieva Rozentāle, "Labvēlīgais tips" producer and author of songs – Ģirts Lūsis, journalist- Sandris Vanzovičs, musicians – Kārlis Auzāns, Jānis Stībelis, Valters Pūce, as well as the musician from Estonia – Ott Lepland.

The Latvian national selection for Eurovision Song Cotest was organised in a cooperation with Ventspils City Council and Ventspils Development Agency, the trusty supporters of LTV on their way to Eurovision Song Contest which is an important event for Latvian musicians and audience.
Latvia will participate in the second semi final of Eurovision Song Contest on May 16 in Malmö, Sweden.
